rComments: Oversimplifies concepts. Repeats every other sentence (we're not stupid, Fortune). Lecture material is interesting, but the lecture itself is quite boring. For test, difficult wording and unclear answers. Worst multiple choice tests that I have ever experienced. I'm doing well in the course but am so dissatisfied with her low-quality teaching.

I don't understand the people who rate Jen so low, she is the best Professor I've ever had in my 4 years at UofT. Her lectures are wonderfully insightful, engaging and stimulating. The work is average compared to most other courses and the five assignments someone complained about were REFLECTION assignments, easy as pie! Take her class if you can!
Very high summer session workload- 2 midterms, 5 assignments of 500 words each, and a final. Lectures not interesting nor useful. Tests mostly focused on the textbook.
Very good professor. Genuinely cared about the topics being taught.
She's extremely funny and makes the lectures enjoyable and fun!
Interesting and engaging prof! Helpful if request clarification of concepts. Tests fairly difficult but if you read/make notes on the textbook and study hard, possible to do really well!
Lectures were interesting but useless when studying for the tests/exams. She tested mainly on little details from the text book and articles (including percentages from experiments so beware).
